Feature: Managing Project Issues

This feature is designed to test the main possible, but basic operations a user can perform
in order to manage project issues. Some fundamental connections/ assignments with other CDB objects
might also be tested. Further possible connections/ assignments are tested in the respective feature.

Background:
    Given a project exists


Scenario Outline: Create New Project Issue
    When <role> creates a new project issue
    Then a new project issue is <creation>

    Examples:
        | role            | creation  |
        | Projektmitglied | generated |


Scenario Outline: Change Project Issue
    Given a project issue exists
    When <role> changes this project issue
    Then this changed project issue is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status |
        | Projektmitglied | saved  |


Scenario Outline: Copy Project Issue
    Given a project issue exists
    When <role> copies this project issue
    Then the project issue is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status |
        | Projektmitglied | copied |


Scenario Outline: Delete Project Issue
    Given a project issue exists
    When <role> deletes this project issue
    Then the project issue is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status  |
        | Projektmitglied | deleted |
